Key Match Events: USA won the match in the Super Over after a tie with Pakistan, both teams scoring 159 runs in their respective innings.
Pre-Game Insights: USA entered the game with high confidence after a series win against Bangladesh and a victory over Canada.
Pakistan faced challenges with training due to rain in Dallas and had inconsistent performances in their previous series against Ireland and England.
Imad Wasim was injured and unable to play, affecting Pakistan's team balance.
Aaron Jones was highlighted as a key player for USA, especially in the middle overs against Pakistan's bowlers.
Azam Khan's performance was under scrutiny after a poor game against England.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain had affected the practice sessions for Pakistan leading up to the match.
The pitch in Dallas offered early seam movement with decent bounce and carry.
Haris Rauf was close to reaching 100 T20I wickets, needing five more to achieve the milestone.
